  "texts": [
    "Knowledge distillation (KD) is adopted in BERT-PKD [33], tinyBERT [18], and distilBERT [31] and [12] in MiniLLM to distill knowledge from the layers of a large transformer model to a smaller one.",
    "See also the survey [45].",
    "All these existing methods produce a single compressed model, unsuitable for edge scenarios with multiple deployment devices having varying computational capability.Neural architecture search (NAS) based on reinforcement learning [46] and evolutionary algorithms [28,44] trains every possible architecture and is very slow.",
    "Weight-sharing NAS was thus developed: in Guo et al. [13], Cai et al.",
    "[5], the building blocks in the same layer are isolated as all architectures are single paths."
  ],
